The only one with a signature is the gathering V, which is marked xvi. This is the sixteenth gathering of the Sacra- mentary proper, which begins with the fifth gathering of the volume, at the page marked 54. Hence it may be inserted that the first four gatherings of the present book did not originally form part of the same volume with the Sacramentary. They are apparently of about the same date with the Sacramentary itself, with the exception of the last two leaveS, which are in a rather later hand.
